                    <h4 style="color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Method 1: Router Web Interface</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Access Your Router:</strong><br>
                            Open a web browser and go to your router's IP address (usually <code>192.168.1.1</code> or <code>192.168.0.1</code>)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Log In:</strong><br>
                            Enter your router's username and password (check the sticker on your router if unsure)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Find DNS Settings:</strong><br>
                            Look for "DNS Settings", "Network Settings", or "Internet Settings". Sometimes these options are found under the "DHCP Settings" or "LAN Settings" section.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Enter SiftDNS Servers:</strong><br>
                            Replace existing DNS with:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Primary DNS: <code>[Primary IP from Stripe <a href="https://billing.stripe.com/p/login/4gMdR845R7eLcMNdAXcQU00" style="color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline;">invoice</a> notes or email]</code></li>
                                <li>Secondary DNS: <code>[Secondary IP from Stripe <a href="https://billing.stripe.com/p/login/4gMdR845R7eLcMNdAXcQU00" style="color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline;">invoice</a> notes or email]</code></li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Save and Restart:</strong><br>
                            Save settings and restart your router if prompted
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    <h4 style="color: var(--primary); margin: 2rem 0 1rem;">Method 2: Router Mobile Apps</h4>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Many newer routers use smartphone apps instead of web interfaces:</p>
                    <ul style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                        <li><strong>ASUS:</strong> ASUS Router app ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí LAN ‚Üí DNS Server</li>
                        <li><strong>Eero:</strong> Open Eero app ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Network Settings ‚Üí DNS</li>
                        <li><strong>Google Nest Wifi:</strong> Google Home app ‚Üí WiFi ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Advanced networking ‚Üí DNS</li>
                        <li><strong>Linksys:</strong> Linksys app ‚Üí Advanced Settings ‚Üí Internet Settings ‚Üí DNS</li>
